# Simple UNO Game in Python

## Overview

This is a simple text-based card game inspired by UNO, implemented in Python. The game is designed for two players and follows basic UNO rules.

## How to Play

- Players are dealt 7 cards each at the start.
- A card from the deck is drawn to start the game.
- Players take turns playing cards that match the color or value of the top card.
- If a player can't make a valid move, they draw a card from the deck.
- The first player to run out of cards wins the game.

## Files

- **uno.py**: The main Python script that contains the game logic.

## How to Run

1. **Clone the repository**:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git

Navigate to the project directory:

cd your-repo-name

Run Game


python uno.py

